gomodel:SYNGO_1362  a    owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment     "Rationale: In figure 2, the authors mention \"We characterized a lamprey ortholog of epsin 1 and showed that it is accumulated at release sites at rest and also at clathrin-coated pits in the periactive zone during synaptic activity\". This is justified to make the annotation 'extrinsic component of presynaptic endocytic zone membrane (GO:0098894)' (confocal+immuno-EM).. Experimental description: In the abstract \"by using the lamprey reticulospinal synapse as a model system\"" ;
        lego:modelstate  "production" ;
        dc:contributor   "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7806-5662" ;
        dc:date          "2017-10-10" ;
        dc:title         "SYNGO_CC_1362" ;
        pav:providedBy   "https://syngo.vu.nl" .

